        <h3>A new statement</h3>
        <p>
          Despite the fact that fewer people use it, I'm really proud of the new statement. I've never seen
          a patient statement like this one before so I'm glad to have entered it into the minds and hands
          of some folks. The statement progressively disclosures information in a human-readable way to the
          patient, so they can drink it in one service item at a time. Currently, most statements throw
          everything onto a sheet of paper and use a lot of esoteric language. Our statement is chunked
          into four easy-to-understand sections:
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li>
            What was charged
          </li>
          <li>
            What insurance paid
          </li>
          <li>
            What you've already paid
          </li>
          <li>
            What you owe
          </li>

        </ul>

        <p>
          Each of these sections can be drilled into revealing visits with dates. These visits can be
          further drilled into so you can see individual service items (e.g., an office visit).
        </p>
